About modules: 
if they have a dydl suffix then 'ln -s mymodule.dydl mymodule.so'

Edited irssi files:
src/fe-common/core/fe-channels.c
src/fe-common/core/fe-core-commands.c
src/fe-common/core/window-activity.c
src/fe-common/core/fe-help.c
src/irc/core/ctcp.c
src/core/core.h
src/core/nicklist.c


How to compile source:
1. install glib (from fink)
2. cd path-to-MacIrssi/irssi-0.8.9
3. ./configure --with-modules --with-proxy --enable-ipv6 --enable-ssl --without-textui --with-perl=no
4. click 'build' in xcode

*******************************************
Building text frontend ........... : no
Building irssi bot ............... : no
Building irssi proxy ............. : no
Building with module support ..... : yes
Building with Perl support ....... : static (in irssi binary)
Perl library directory ........... : (site default - /Library/Perl/5.8.1/darwin-thread-multi-2level)
Install prefix ................... : /usr/local

Building with IPv6 support ....... : yes
Building with SSL support ........ : yes
Building with 64bit DCC support .. : yes
Building with garbage collector .. : no
*******************************************
